---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Security" description="How we secure the HelixGitpx platform.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold">Security</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">Defense-in-depth from the data plane to the policy layer.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold">Data protection</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>TLS 1.3 everywhere north-south; mTLS via SPIFFE/SPIRE east-west.</li>
      <li>AES-256 at rest on Postgres, MinIO, and Kafka volumes.</li>
      <li>KMS-managed keys; rotation every 90 days.</li>
      <li>Per-org data residency (EU / UK / US) with audited enforcement.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold">Identity</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>OIDC / SAML via Keycloak.</li>
      <li>WebAuthn for staff. TOTP for customers; SMS only as fallback.</li>
      <li>Just-in-time privileged access via Teleport; all sessions audited.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold">Authorization</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>OPA Rego bundles, signed, versioned, diff-reviewed in CI.</li>
      <li>Default-deny on every external surface.</li>
      <li>Per-tenant policy overlays supported on Enterprise.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold">Supply chain</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>SLSA Level 3 at GA; Level 4 tracked post-GA.</li>
      <li>Cosign signatures on every container image.</li>
      <li>SBOMs published for every release.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold">Program — planning / not-yet-active</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>External pen-test: scope committed (<code>docs/security/pentest-scope-2026q2.md</code>); no vendor engaged yet.</li>
      <li>Bug bounty: rules committed (<code>docs/security/bug-bounty-program.md</code>); no public program active yet.</li>
      <li>SOC 2 Type I: evidence mapping committed (<code>docs/security/soc2-type1-evidence-index.md</code>); no auditor engaged.</li>
      <li>ISO 27001: gap analysis committed (<code>docs/security/iso27001-gap-analysis.md</code>); no certification path started.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-500">All four items are open-source planning artefacts, not active certifications. An operator of a hosted HelixGitpx Service can pursue them on their own timeline.</p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-slate-500">Contact: <a href="mailto:security@helixgitpx.io" class="text-primary hover:underline">security@helixgitpx.io</a> · <a href="/trust" class="text-primary hover:underline">Trust center</a></p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
